snippet.title: Boots Ennis' Prediction on David Avanesyan's KO Round
snippet.description:
#jaronennis #bootsennis #davidavanesyan #janibek #matchroom #eddiehearn #bobarum #toprank #espn #dazn

Tomorrow night we have Jaron Boots Ennis vs David Avanesyan in Philadelphia. This fight is for Boot's IBF strap. Boots declared he wanted to become undisputed at welterweight before he eventually move up.

David Avanesyan last fought back in December of 2023 against Serge Ambomo... who had a 13-63 record. People in the States remember Avanesyan being knocked out cold by Terence Bud Crawford back in 2022 in Omaha, Nebraska.

It appears that the Boots name is being tied to Crawford, in order to build his profile. Very similar to how Shakur, Haney and other fighters at 135 are building their profiles off of Tank's name.

The undercard is as follows: Skye Nicolson vs. Dyana Vargas at Featherweight.
Christopher Diaz vs. Derlyn Hernandez at Super Featherweight. Khalil Coe vs. Manuel Gallegos at Light Heavyweight. And Jalil Hackett vs. Peter Dobson.

Fight card starts at 8:00 PM EST.

Now that Boots is with Eddie Hearn and Matchroom. Let's see if Eddie can make Boots the star that Steven Espinosa and Showtime couldn't do.

In other news. Janibek “Qazaq Style” Alimkhanuly will put his WBO and IBF world titles on the line against New Zealand’s Andrei Mikhailovich on July 13 at Pearl Concert Theater at Palms Casino Resort in Las Vegas.

Janibek wants to become the undisputed Champ at 160. Top Rank has been keeping Janibek very active. He currently holds the IBF and WBO Middleweight titles.

The fight will be on Top Rank and shown on ESPN+. The fight will be held at the Palms Casino Resort in Las Vegas on Saturday (Fight card starts at 6:40 p.m. ET).

The undercard is as follows:

Raymond Muratalla vs. Tevin Farmer; Lightweights
